00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.333
Knox cloud services 26.06 release highlights.

2
00:00:03.333 --> 00:00:06.033
Check out what's new in Knox Configure.

3
00:00:06.033 --> 00:00:09.966
Ability to include a hyperlink when pushing an update notification.

4
00:00:10.466 --> 00:00:14.032
When sending a custom notification after pushing a profile update,

5
00:00:14.433 --> 00:00:17.382
you now have the option to include a hyperlink that directs 

6
00:00:17.382 --> 00:00:20.242
device users to a webpage for more information.

7
00:00:20.243 --> 00:00:21.778
After adding a hyperlink,

8
00:00:21.779 --> 00:00:26.299
device users will see a Learn more link on their device when the notification appears.

9
00:00:26.800 --> 00:00:30.357
Additional options for sending profile update notifications.

10
00:00:30.357 --> 00:00:33.442
Previously, you could only send a custom notification to 

11
00:00:33.443 --> 00:00:35.699
device users when pushing a profile update. 

12
00:00:35.833 --> 00:00:38.381
In this release, you'll also have the option to send a 

13
00:00:38.381 --> 00:00:41.766
custom notification whenever you change a device's assigned profile.

14
00:00:42.600 --> 00:00:46.600
Additionally, if you push a profile update or assign a different profile 

15
00:00:46.600 --> 00:00:50.574
from the BULK ACTIONS tab on the Devices page,  you'll now have the option to

16
00:00:50.574 --> 00:00:54.532
include a custom notification along with a hyperlink to a webpage.

17
00:00:55.400 --> 00:00:58.100
Prevent the upload of malicious APK files.

18
00:00:58.400 --> 00:01:02.400
A new malware check feature detects and prevents infected APK files from 

19
00:01:02.400 --> 00:01:04.400
uploading to the Knox Configure server, 

20
00:01:04.400 --> 00:01:08.300
thereby avoiding the installation of malicious apps on your customers' devices.

21
00:01:08.300 --> 00:01:11.323
If malware is detected, the upload is blocked, 

22
00:01:11.323 --> 00:01:15.233
and you'll receive a notification in the console and in the activity logs.

23
00:01:15.233 --> 00:01:19.233
Disable cover screen mirroring for Galaxy Z Fold devices.

24
00:01:19.233 --> 00:01:22.375
You can now disable the 'Cover screen mirroring' feature 

25
00:01:22.376 --> 00:01:24.899
when creating profiles for Galaxy Z-Fold devices.

26
00:01:24.900 --> 00:01:27.396
Normally, when this feature is enabled,

27
00:01:27.396 --> 00:01:30.884
the shortcuts on the cover screen are copied over to the main screen.

28
00:01:30.884 --> 00:01:32.925
By disabling this feature in the profile,

29
00:01:32.926 --> 00:01:36.593
your device users can customize their cover and main screens separately,

30
00:01:36.593 --> 00:01:39.314
allowing them to set up their screen layouts according to their 

31
00:01:39.315 --> 00:01:41.099
personal needs and requirements.

32
00:01:41.100 --> 00:01:44.866
Set installation order of apps during and after configuration.

33
00:01:45.500 --> 00:01:49.500
You can now specify the installation order of custom apps in a profile, 

34
00:01:49.500 --> 00:01:52.166
ensuring required apps are installed first.

35
00:01:52.166 --> 00:01:55.279
Additionally, apps with policy restrictions

36
00:01:55.280 --> 00:01:58.466
and custom configurations can be installed before internal apps.

37
00:01:59.766 --> 00:02:03.766
To learn more about the features in this release, or to get additional help at any time, 

38
00:02:03.766 --> 00:02:07.066
see our documentation at docs.samsungknox.com. 

39
00:02:07.333 --> 00:02:08.499
Thanks for watching!

